│ the Issue\nThe crash occurs due to an          │
│ assertion failure in                           │
│ `SCEVExpanderCleaner::cleanup`. The assertion  │
│ checks that all users of an instruction being  │
│ removed are themselves instructions inserted   │
│ during the expansion process. This ensures     │
│ that no external instructions depend on the    │
│ ones being removed.\n\n### 2. Analyzing        │
│ `opt`'s Log\nThe log indicates that the        │
│ `loop-vectorize` pass is attempting to         │
│ vectorize a loop, and during this process, it  │
│ uses `SCEVExpander` to generate new            │
│ instructions. However, the assertion failure   │
│ suggests that some of these instructions are   │
│ being used by values that were not inserted    │
│ during the expansion process.\n\n### 3. Root   │
│ Cause Analysis\nFrom the debugger:\n- The      │
│ instruction `%0 = add i32 %N, 1` is being      │
│ removed.\n- One of its users is `%smax1 = call │
│ i32 @llvm.smax.i32(i32 %sub4, i32 %0)`, which  │
│ is not part of the `InsertedSet`.\n- The       │
│ operand `%0` of `%smax1` is part of the        │
│ `InsertedSet`, but `%smax1` itself is not.\n-  │
│ This indicates that `%smax1` was not inserted  │
│ during the expansion process, yet it depends   │
│ on `%0`, which is being removed.\n\nThis       │
│ mismatch occurs because `SCEVExpander` does    │
│ not account for all possible uses of the       │
│ instructions it generates. Specifically, it    │
│ does not handle cases where external           │
│ instructions (like `%smax1`) depend on the     │
│ expanded instructions.\n\n### 4. Proposed Edit │
│ Points(s)\nTo fix this, we need to ensure that │
│ `SCEVExpanderCleaner::cleanup` does not remove │
│ instructions that are used by external values. │
│ This can be achieved by modifying the          │
│ assertion to exclude such cases or by adding a │
│ check to skip the removal of such              │
│ instructions.\n\nEdit Point:\n- File:          │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/ScalarEvolutionExpa │
│ nder.cpp`\n- Lines: 2402-2407\n- Change the    │
│ assertion                                      │
│ to:\n```cpp\nassert(all_of(I->users(),\n       │
│ [&InsertedSet](Value *U) {\n                   │
│ auto *Inst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(U);\n       │
│ return Inst && InsertedSet.contains(Inst);\n   │
│ }) &&\n       \"removed instruction should     │
│ only be used by instructions inserted \"\n     │
│ \"during expansion or external                 │
│ instructions\");\n```\n\n### 5.                │
│ Conclusion\nThis fix ensures that the          │
│ assertion accounts for external instructions   │
│ that depend on the expanded instructions. It   │
│ prevents the crash while maintaining the       │
│ integrity of the `SCEVExpanderCleaner`         │
│ logic."})                                      │
