│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                    │
│                                                │
│ -------------------- BEGIN                     │
│ --------------------                           │
│ ### 1. Understanding the Issue                 │
│ The crash occurs due to an assertion failure   │
│ in `SCEVExpanderCleaner::cleanup`. The         │
│ assertion checks that all users of an          │
│ instruction being removed are themselves       │
│ instructions inserted during the expansion     │
│ process. This ensures that no external         │
│ instructions depend on the ones being removed. │
│                                                │
│ ### 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log                   │
│ The log indicates that the `loop-vectorize`    │
│ pass is attempting to vectorize a loop, and    │
│ during this process, it uses `SCEVExpander` to │
│ generate new instructions. However, the        │
│ assertion failure suggests that some of these  │
│ instructions are being used by values that     │
│ were not inserted during the expansion         │
│ process.                                       │
│                                                │
│ ### 3. Root Cause Analysis                     │
│ From the debugger:                             │
│ - The instruction `%0 = add i32 %N, 1` is      │
│ being removed.                                 │
│ - One of its users is `%smax1 = call i32       │
│ @llvm.smax.i32(i32 %sub4, i32 %0)`, which is   │
│ not part of the `InsertedSet`.                 │
│ - The operand `%0` of `%smax1` is part of the  │
│ `InsertedSet`, but `%smax1` itself is not.     │
│ - This indicates that `%smax1` was not         │
│ inserted during the expansion process, yet it  │
│ depends on `%0`, which is being removed.       │
│                                                │
│ This mismatch occurs because `SCEVExpander`    │
│ does not account for all possible uses of the  │
│ instructions it generates. Specifically, it    │
│ does not handle cases where external           │
│ instructions (like `%smax1`) depend on the     │
│ expanded instructions.                         │
│                                                │
│ ### 4. Proposed Edit Points(s)                 │
│ To fix this, we need to ensure that            │
│ `SCEVExpanderCleaner::cleanup` does not remove │
│ instructions that are used by external values. │
│ This can be achieved by modifying the          │
│ assertion to exclude such cases or by adding a │
│ check to skip the removal of such              │
│ instructions.                                  │
│                                                │
│ Edit Point:                                    │
│ - File:                                        │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/ScalarEvolutionExpa │
│ nder.cpp`                                      │
│ - Lines: 2402-2407                             │
│ - Change the assertion to:                     │
│ ```cpp                                         │
│ assert(all_of(I->users(),                      │
│               [&InsertedSet](Value *U) {       │
│                 auto *Inst =                   │
│ dyn_cast<Instruction>(U);                      │
│                 return Inst &&                 │
│ InsertedSet.contains(Inst);                    │
│               }) &&                            │
│        "removed instruction should only be     │
│ used by instructions inserted "                │
│        "during expansion or external           │
│ instructions");                                │
│ ```                                            │
│                                                │
│ ### 5. Conclusion                              │
│ This fix ensures that the assertion accounts   │
│ for external instructions that depend on the   │
│ expanded instructions. It prevents the crash   │
│ while maintaining the integrity of the         │
│ `SCEVExpanderCleaner` logic.                   │
│ --------------------  END                      │
│ --------------------                           │
